=========================================================
WHY MULTITHREADING? (C++ INTERVIEW NOTES)
=========================================================

Definition
----------

Multithreading allows multiple threads to execute concurrently within the same process.

It enables a program to perform multiple tasks simultaneously while sharing the same memory.

---------------------------------------------------------

Why Do We Need Multithreading?

Without Multithreading:

- Only one task executes at a time.
- CPU may remain idle while waiting for I/O.
- Application becomes slow and unresponsive.

With Multithreading:

- Multiple tasks run concurrently.
- Better CPU utilization.
- Faster execution.
- Improved responsiveness.

---------------------------------------------------------

Real-world Examples

1. Web Browser
- One thread handles UI.
- One thread downloads data.
- One thread renders web pages.

2. Music Player
- One thread plays music.
- One thread updates the UI.
- One thread downloads the next song.

3. Game Engine
- Rendering thread
- Physics thread
- AI thread
- Audio thread

4. Web Server
- Multiple client requests handled in parallel.

---------------------------------------------------------

Advantages

✓ Better CPU utilization
✓ Improved application responsiveness
✓ Parallel execution of independent tasks
✓ Higher throughput
✓ Shared memory makes communication efficient
✓ Lower memory usage than multiple processes

---------------------------------------------------------

Disadvantages

✗ Race conditions
✗ Deadlocks
✗ Synchronization overhead
✗ More difficult debugging

---------------------------------------------------------

